# Atlassian MCP
Use `mcp-cli` to access Datadog Atlassian through the `atlassian` MCP server.

Config:
- Server: `atlassian`
- Cloud ID: `66c05bee-f5ff-4718-b6fc-81351e5ef659`
- Config file: `~/.config/mcp/mcp_servers.json`
- Transport: `npx -y mcp-remote https://mcp.atlassian.com/v1/mcp`

Discovery:
```fish
mcp-cli info atlassian
mcp-cli info atlassian searchConfluenceUsingCql
mcp-cli info atlassian searchJiraIssuesUsingJql
```

Common calls:
```fish
mcp-cli call atlassian getAccessibleAtlassianResources '{}'

mcp-cli call atlassian searchConfluenceUsingCql '{
  "cloudId": "66c05bee-f5ff-4718-b6fc-81351e5ef659",
  "cql": "text ~ \"query\"",
  "limit": 10
}'

mcp-cli call atlassian getConfluencePage '{
  "cloudId": "66c05bee-f5ff-4718-b6fc-81351e5ef659",
  "pageId": "PAGE_ID",
  "contentFormat": "markdown"
}'

mcp-cli call atlassian searchJiraIssuesUsingJql '{
  "cloudId": "66c05bee-f5ff-4718-b6fc-81351e5ef659",
  "jql": "project = ABC AND text ~ \"query\"",
  "maxResults": 10
}'

mcp-cli call atlassian getJiraIssue '{
  "cloudId": "66c05bee-f5ff-4718-b6fc-81351e5ef659",
  "issueIdOrKey": "ABC-123",
  "responseContentFormat": "markdown"
}'
```

Rules:
- Prefer read-only tools.
- Do not create, update, comment, transition, or edit unless the user explicitly asks.
- Use stdin/heredocs for complex JSON to avoid shell quoting issues.
- `MCP_NO_DAEMON` and `MCP_STRICT_ENV` are set globally in `~/.config/fish/conf.d/mcp.fish`. Do not set them per-call.
